  "description": "Perennial herb from Polygonaceae, native to Mediterranean and Central Europe. Produces long-petioled leaves with distinctive red-veined pattern and lemony, sour flavor from oxalic acid. Longevous perennial (zone 4); persistent root system allows multiple harvests per season without replanting.",
